=== TASK ===
# Login / Signup

## Overview
Create a robust, secure, and UX-driven Login / Signup experience that serves as the authentication entry point for Guests, Hosts, and Concierge users. This page must support account creation, authentication, session persistence, password management (verification, reset), and role-based routing to appropriate flows. It should prioritize accessibility, performance, and security while aligning with Roam Resort’s premium editorial design language. The implementation must include client-side validation, server-side validation hooks, error handling with deterministic UX states, and strong session/security controls (rate-limiting, audit logging, and active session management).

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- A unified Login / Signup interface that serves as the authentication gateway. It presents both forms in a single, tabbed view with a clear pathway to the appropriate downstream flows (guest onboarding, host listing access, concierge admin). It should be accessible to unauthenticated users and guard protected routes via role-based access control after authentication.

Goals:
- Provide secure email/password authentication with session persistence across refreshes.
- Support account creation with validated email ownership, password strength checks, and optional email verification flow.
- Implement password reset workflow (email-based reset link with token validation and UI flow to set a new password).
- Enforce role-based access control so Guests, Hosts, and Concierge users land in their respective experiences after login.
- Offer graceful error handling, live validation, and retry strategies with clear user-facing messaging.
- Prepare for future social auth (placeholders) while keeping V1 functionality self-contained and secure.

Connected features:
- User Authentication & Authorization: Secure login, signup, email verification, password reset, session persistence, and role-based routing.
- Error Handling, Validation & UX States: Client/server validation, loading indicators, retry flows, and contextual error messages.
- Session & Security Management: Persist sessions, monitor active sessions, and apply rate-limiting and audit logging.

UI guidance to follow:
- Tabbed UI with two tabs: Login and Signup. Include a simple toggle to switch between modes if needed, but ideally a persistent tab layout.
- Form fields:
  - Email
  - Password
  - Name (Signup only)
  - Password strength indicator (Signup)
  - Remember me checkbox (Login)
  - Forgot password link
- Visual design cues: Use the provided color palette, typography, and layout guidelines to render a premium, editorial feel. Include microcopy for terms/legal links.
- Security UX: Show loading states during API calls, disable form during submission, and provide retry options on failure.
- Accessibility: Proper labels, aria-live regions for errors, keyboard navigation, and high-contrast states as per design system.

UI elements & visual guidance:
- Lawful microcopy for consent/terms: Terms, Privacy, and consent statements near signup.
- Hero/landing hints: Subtle background texture or imagery consistent with Roam Resort’s aesthetics; content-focused form card with soft shadows and rounded corners.
- Placeholder content: Use neutral placeholder text until dynamic data is integrated.
- Disabled social auth buttons in V1 with clear disabled state indicators (no action on click).

API integrations (local to this task):
- No external API dependencies required beyond internal authentication APIs; ensure the page is designed to consume a standard auth API contract (login, signup, verify, reset, session, roles).

---

## Components to Build
- AuthTabs (UI container with two tabs: Login, Signup)
  - Props: onTabChange, activeTab
  - State: local validation, loading states
- AuthForm (shared form logic for both Login and Signup)
  - Props: mode ("login" | "signup"), onSubmit, initialValues
  - State: email, password, name (optional), rememberMe, errors, loading
  - Validation: client-side checks (email format, password strength, required fields)
  - UI: email, password, name (signup), remember me, forgot password link (login), password strength meter
- PasswordResetModal or Flow
  - Props: show, onClose, email
  - State: token, newPassword, confirmPassword, errors
- SocialAuthPlaceholders (optional in V1)
  - Props: disabled; provide visual disabled state
- ErrorBanner
  - Props: message, subMessage, onRetry
- LoadingSpinner
  - Inline loading indicators for buttons and sections
- SignUpSuccessCard
  - Confirmation state after signup (redirect guidance or next steps)
- RedirectHandler
  - Post-auth routing to proper flows based on user role
- api/auth.js (or /services/auth.ts)
  - Methods: login, signup, requestPasswordReset, resetPassword, verifyEmail, getCurrentSession, logout
  - Ensure all responses are validated (data ?? [] patterns) and guard array methods with Array.isArray checks
  - Enforce null/undefined guards per runtime safety rules
- types/models.ts
  - UserRole: "guest" | "host" | "concierge"
  - AuthResponse shape: { sessionToken, user: { id, email, name, role } } | error
- hooks/useAuth.ts
  - useState with initial arrays/objects as appropriate, and ensure default values
  - useEffect to hydrate session from storage
- utils/validation.ts
  - Email format, password strength scoring, cross-field validation
- analytics/auditLogger.ts
  - Simple audit hook to log login attempts, resets, and signups (rate-limited)
- utils/guards.ts
  - isAuthenticated, hasRole, etc., to support client-side redirects

---

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- UI/UX:
  - Build a responsive, accessible, tabbed Auth UI with a card layout that matches the design system.
  - Implement password strength meter with real-time feedback.
  - Provide client-side validation for email, password, and name (on signup).
  - Show inline field errors and a global error area via ErrorBanner when needed.
  - Show loading indicators during API calls; disable inputs while submitting.
  - Implement remember-me persistence (e.g., long-lived token in secure storage) with a fallback to session-based persistence.
  - Include a Forgot Password flow with email-based reset initiation.
  - Provide Terms & Privacy links near signup with proper routing.
- Data handling:
  - All API responses must be validated; handle null data safely: e.g., const session = (response?.data?.session) ?? null
  - Guard array results: const userList = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
- State management:
  - Use React (functional components) with useState and useEffect; ensure useState([]) defaults for array-based state
  - Centralized auth state in a React context or a dedicated hook (useAuth) with ISR-friendly storage
- Security UX:
  - Rate-limit indicators and messages for login attempts (simulate server-side headers if needed)
  - Audit logging hooks to capture login attempts, signups, password resets (client-side emit; server should persist)
- Accessibility:
  - Proper ARIA attributes, keyboard navigation, and screen-reader friendly error announcements
- Routing:
  - After successful login, redirect based on role to Guest inquiry flow, Host dashboard, or Concierge admin
  - If user already authenticated, redirect away from login/signup page

### Backend
- API Endpoints:
  - POST /api/auth/login
  - POST /api/auth/signup
  - POST /api/auth/request-password-reset
  - POST /api/auth/reset-password
  - GET /api/auth/verify-email?token=...
  - GET /api/auth/session (get current session)
  - POST /api/auth/logout
- Database schema (simplified):
  - users: id UUID PK, email unique, passwordHash, name, role ENUM('guest','host','concierge'), emailVerified boolean, createdAt, updatedAt
  - sessions: id UUID PK, userId FK, token, expiresAt, lastUsedAt, ipAddress, userAgent
  - audit_logs: id UUID PK, userId, action, timestamp, details
  - password_resets: id UUID PK, email, token, expiresAt
  - host_listings (for Hosts): id, ownerUserId, etc. (not required for auth but for role routing)
- Security:
  - Passwords hashed using bcrypt or Argon2
  - Tokens generated securely (cryptographically strong)
  - Email verification flow integration (generate token, send email; this prompt does not implement email sending logic but defines contract)
  - Rate-limiting on login endpoints (per IP and per user)
  - Audit logs on login attempts, signups, password resets
- Validation:
  - Server-side validation for email format, password strength, required fields
  - Return structured errors with user-friendly messages and error codes (e.g., INVALID_PASSWORD, EMAIL_NOT_VERIFIED)

### Integration
- Client-Server Contract:
  - Align request/response shapes to be predictable and type-safe
  - Use data ?? [] and Array.isArray guards when consuming API responses
  - Centralized error forwarding to UI with user-friendly messages
- Session & Redirects:
  - Persist sessionToken in secure storage; on app load, fetch session and hydrate user context
  - Role-based redirects immediately after login; guard protected routes on client
- Error Handling:
  - Display server-provided error codes/messages when available; fallback to generic messages
- Security:
  - Ensure client does not store plaintext passwords
  - Use https, proper CORS settings (assumed in backend)

---

## User Experience Flow
1. User lands on Login / Signup page.
2. They can switch to Signup tab to create a new account:
   - Enter name, email, password
   - Password strength meter updates in real-time
   - Client-side validation shows errors (invalid email, weak password, missing name)
   - On submit, show loading state; if success, show signup success card and route to email verification or onboarding
3. If they choose to Login:
   - Enter email and password, optional Remember Me
   - Click Login; show loading indicator
   - If credentials valid, backend returns session token
   - Client stores session; user is redirected to role-appropriate flow:
     - Guest: Stay within guest inquiry flow
     - Host: Access Host dashboard
     - Concierge: Access Admin panel
   - If invalid, show contextual error (e.g., wrong password, unverified email)
4. Forgot Password:
   - Click link; enter email; receive reset flow guidance
   - User submits reset request; UI shows success message and next steps
5. Password Reset:
   - User follows tokenized link (not fully implemented here); present form to set new password
6. Sessions & Security:
   - Active session management is available; user can log out from the app
   - Retry flows and error messaging for failed attempts, with rate-limit notices if applicable
7. Admin/Concierge:
   - Concierge users can view inquiries, update status, add notes, and export CSV (via admin panel)

