## Technical Specifications

Data Models:
- User:
  - id: string (UUID)
  - email: string
  - passwordHash: string
  - name: string
  - role: "guest" | "host" | "concierge"
  - emailVerified: boolean
  - createdAt: Date
  - updatedAt: Date
- Session:
  - id: string
  - userId: string
  - token: string
  - expiresAt: Date
  - lastUsedAt: Date
  - ipAddress: string
  - userAgent: string
- AuditLog:
  - id: string
  - userId: string
  - action: string
  - timestamp: Date
  - details: string
- PasswordReset:
  - id: string
  - email: string
  - token: string
  - expiresAt: Date

API Endpoints:
- POST /api/auth/login
  - Body: { email, password, rememberMe }
  - Response: { sessionToken, user: { id, email, name, role, emailVerified } }
- POST /api/auth/signup
  - Body: { name, email, password }
  - Response: { user: { id, email, name, role }, needsEmailVerification: boolean }
- POST /api/auth/request-password-reset
  - Body: { email }
  - Response: { ok: true }
- POST /api/auth/reset-password
  - Body: { token, newPassword }
  - Response: { ok: true }
- GET /api/auth/verify-email?token=...
  - Response: { ok: true } or error
- GET /api/auth/session
  - Response: { user: { id, email, name, role }, token, expiresAt } or null
- POST /api/auth/logout
  - Response: { ok: true }

Security:
- Passwords hashed with bcrypt/Argon2
- Tokens generated securely
- Rate-limiting on login attempts per IP and per user
- Email verification gating for role-based access when required
- Audit logs for login attempts, signups, password resets
- Client should not expose secrets; store tokens securely (e.g., HttpOnly cookies preferred; if localStorage is used, ensure proper security)

Validation Rules:
- Email must be valid format and unique on signup
- Password strength: minimum length, complexity (uppercase, lowercase, number, special), with a visual meter
- Name required for signup; optional for login
- RememberMe influences session persistence duration
- All endpoints must return explicit error codes/messages; client maps to user-friendly messages

